div1.p:


     JOHN
      PERCIVAL




sworn;

Did you pick it up? - Yes, after we had secured him. He cut me over the fingers with his hanger; I got it out of his hand when I got him upon the ground; this is the hanger (producing it) I picked up 3 s. 6 d. afterwards some other people picked up some more, and gave to Mr. Hughes; this is the pistol (a small pocket pistol) I marked it;
Thomas Brumsdell
came up; Harris said, he was not the man; he was running the same as the rest; I told him it was of no use for him to say that; Brumsdell and I tied his hands.

As I was coming down Laystall-street I met the two prisoners;
Mary Fisher
had the bundle in her apron; I saw it was black; I saw no more.

You do not know any more about the beginning of this than what you have told me;
Mary Sinclair
calling out was the first that you knew of it? - It was.
